&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br&gt;About the Position&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position reports to the Strategic Account Manager and Night Area Manager and is responsible for the team&#39;s book of business for the night shift. This entails bidding shipments, winning shipments, negotiating rates with carriers, and trace and functions for shipments on assigned teams within the brokerage division. This includes the following:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate competitive market rates with potential carriers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Properly vet all tendered carriers in alignment with ITS best-in-class standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cover/Recover broken-down shipments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cover spot market (Adhoc) shipments awarded during night shift.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cover open contracted loads as assigned by SAM/Sr NAM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with high-level issue resolution escalated from Night Operations Representatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and trace current shipments in the ITS network.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining relationships with drivers and providing support as needed. &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Producing timely and accurate communication to all customers within the assigned network.  &lt;/li&gt;
