&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;About the Position&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ITS has an immediate opening for a Solutions Engineer.&amp;nbsp; The Solutions Engineer will be responsible for collaborating with the sales team to understand client needs, designing and presenting innovative solutions, and working closely with operations, IT, and pricing to ensure feasibility and efficiency. The role involves developing and engineering comprehensive solutions for warehouse design, inventory management, and automation. Key responsibilities include analyzing customer data, product flows, and operational requirements to create optimal solutions. This includes designing warehouse layouts, material handling systems, and processes. The role also requires participation in client meetings to present solutions and manage expectations, acting as a liaison between operations, the IT team, and customers to ensure that solution delivery aligns with customer needs. Additionally, the position involves collaborating with automation providers to deliver the most optimal options while staying updated on technological advancements to incorporate into solution designs. Lastly, the individual is responsible for overseeing the handoff to the implementation team and assisting in onboarding new clients to ensure a seamless transition from proposal to execution.&amp;nbsp; The ideal candidate will have a strong background in logistics, automation technologies, and process optimization, and will be skilled in translating client requirements into practical, cost-effective solutions.&amp;nbsp; The Solutions Engineer should be comfortable working independently with minimal direction. &amp;nbsp;This position reports to the VP of Solutions Engineering. We’re looking for a solid player with succession capabilities beyond this role; one with the capacity to engage teams and build followership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Principle Accountabilities&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the sales team to understand client challenges, needs, and objectives. Help design and present tailored logistics solutions that leverage automation and enhance operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop custom distribution and fulfillment solutions. Ensure solutions align with client goals and internal capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;

